div.head:
Memorandum of Conversation, by the Assistant Secretary of
    State for Far Eastern Affairs (
    Robertson
) and the Counselor (
    MacArthur
)

frus:attachment.p:
Desiring to assure the independence of the States of Vietnam, Laos and
                        Cambodia which are now subject to armed attack and invasion by forces which
                        serve international Communism;

Convinced that the situation calls for their exercise in this area of the
                        inherent right of collective self-defense recognized by Article 51 of the
                        Charter of the United Nations;

list.item:
That if the lands of any of them in the Southeast Asia and Western
                            Pacific area fell under the domination of international Communism that
                            would be a threat to the peace and security of them all;
